19 SECTION 29. IC 24-3-2-9 IS AMENDED TO READ AS
20 FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 9. (a) In determining
21 cost to the retailer and cost to the distributor, the court or the
22 department, as the case may be, shall receive and consider as bearing
23 on the bona fides of such cost evidence tending to show that any person
24 complained against under any of the provisions of this chapter
25 purchased cigarettes with respect to the sale of which complaint is
26 made at a fictitious price, or upon terms, or in such manner, or under
27 such invoices, as to conceal the true cost, discounts, or terms of
28 purchase, and shall also receive and consider as bearing on the bona
29 fides of such cost evidence of the normal, customary, and prevailing
30 terms and discounts in connection with other sales of a similar nature
31 in the trade area or state.
32 (b) Merchandise given gratis or payment made to a retailer or
33 distributor for display, or advertising, or promotion purposes, or
34 otherwise shall not be considered in determining the cost of cigarettes
35 to the retailer or distributor.
36 (c) A buydown must be considered in determining the cost to the
37 retailer or the cost to the distributor, as applicable, provided that
38 the sum of any buydown and consideration paid by the purchaser
39 is not below the cost to the retailer or distributor.
